What I Built
Backend (Express.js + PostgreSQL)
The backend artifact contains a complete REST API server with:

Authentication system with JWT tokens and bcrypt password hashing
Role-based access control for Admin, User, and Store Owner
Complete CRUD operations for users, stores, and ratings
Input validation matching all specified requirements
Database schema with proper constraints and indexes
Default admin account auto-created on startup

Frontend (React + Tailwind CSS)
The frontend artifact contains a complete React application with:

Login/Register pages with real-time validation
Admin Dashboard with statistics, user management, store management, filtering, and sorting
User Dashboard with store browsing, searching, and interactive star ratings
Store Owner Dashboard with average rating display and user ratings list
Password change functionality for all user roles
Responsive design using Tailwind CSS

Setup Instructions
The third artifact provides complete setup documentation including installation steps, environment configuration, database setup, and API endpoint reference.
Key Features Implemented
RequirementStatusSingle login system for all roles✅Admin: Dashboard with stats✅Admin: Add users/stores✅Admin: Filter & sort tables✅User: Registration with validation✅User: Rate stores 1-5✅User: Modify ratings✅Store Owner: View ratings & average✅All validations (name, email, password, address)✅Sorting on all tables✅
Quick Start

Set up PostgreSQL and create the database
Copy the backend code into server.js, configure .env
Run npm install and npm run dev for backend
Create React app, add Tailwind, copy frontend code
Run npm start for frontend
Login with admin@system.com / Admin@123